description:
Been here a few times, nothing too impressive that really stands out. The typical Vietnamese food you find in any Vietnamese restaurants. Don't get me wrong, it's a pretty solid restaurant, offering a good variety to choose from soup noodles to stir fry. The menu is quite extensive. If you can't decide, look around the tables and see what others are eating! 

I've tried their (1) Pho, especially with the beef tendons cooked to perfection, broth is standard; (2) Garlic clams, wished they could be a bit more generous at that price; (3) Banh Xeo, filling and hearty, but didn't care for the mung beans added to it; 

Service here is always friendly and very fast at getting your food to your table. If you are craving for some good pho and in this area, do check this place out! They are related to Yummy & Yummy on Irving.
